          <title>Wizards finally hold a team under 100 points, the last NBA team to do so this season</title>
          <description><![CDATA[WASHINGTON (AP) — It took 57 games for the Washington Wizards to hold a team under 100 points this season. Of course, Marcus Smart wasn't around for most of those. Smart and the Wizards held Brooklyn to 12 points in the fourth quarter of their 107-99 victory over the Nets on Monday night.]]></description>
